message: Franklin Pierce did not swear on a law book as this page erroneously stated. He swore on the bible. It is true that he broke previous precedent by placing his hand on the bible, rather than kissing the book. It is also true that he changed out the word "swear" for "affirm" in his oath. But it was all done on the bible. Here is a link to the appropriate source from the Architect of the Capitol. https://www.aoc.gov/what-we-do/programs-ceremonies/inauguration#dates

message: /* Administration of the oath */ This article contains a list of every administration of the Oath, and the person who administered it.
